with sessions as (
    select
        p.country,
        date_trunc('month', s.event_datetime::timestamp) as year_month,
        event_length_seconds as session_seconds
    from "synthetic"."leap_stage"."fact_session" s
    join "synthetic"."leap_dim"."dim_players" p on s.player_id = p.player_id
),

monthly_agg as (
    select
        country,
        year_month,
        sum(session_seconds) as total_play_time_seconds
    from sessions
    group by country, year_month
)

select * from monthly_agg

with transactions as (
    select
        p.country,
        date_trunc('week', t.event_datetime::timestamp) as year_week,
        round(sum(t.purchase_price), 2) as total_revenue
    from "synthetic"."leap_raw"."event_transaction" t
    join "synthetic"."leap_dim"."dim_players" p on t.player_id = p.player_id

    group by p.country, year_week
)
select * from transactions

with sessions as (
    select
        player_id,
        date_trunc('day'::varchar, event_datetime::timestamp) as calendar_date,
        event_length_seconds,
        kills,
        deaths
    from "synthetic"."leap_stage"."fact_session"

    
      where date_trunc('day'::varchar, event_datetime::timestamp) > (
        select max(calendar_date) from "synthetic"."leap_mart"."player_activity_daily"
      )
    
),

daily_agg as (
    select
        player_id,
        calendar_date,
        sum(event_length_seconds) as total_play_time_seconds,
        count(*) as sessions_count,
        sum(kills) as total_kills,
        sum(deaths) as total_deaths,
        case 
          when sum(deaths) = 0 then null
          else round(cast(sum(kills) as float) / sum(deaths), 2)
        end as kill_death_ratio
    from sessions
    group by player_id, calendar_date
)

select * from daily_agg

with source as (
    select raw_response
    from "synthetic"."leap_raw"."event_session"
    
      -- Only get sessions newer than what we've already processed
      where (raw_response ->>'$.end_time')::timestamp
            > (select max(event_datetime) from "synthetic"."leap_stage"."event_heartbeat")
    
),

expanded as (
    select 
        (hb.value->>'$.session_id')::varchar       as session_id,
        (hb.value->>'$.timestamp')::timestamp       as event_datetime,
        (hb.value->>'$.player_id')::varchar          as player_id,
        (hb.value->>'$.team_id')::varchar            as team_id,
        (hb.value->>'$.position_x')::float           as position_x,
        (hb.value->>'$.position_y')::float           as position_y,
        (hb.value->>'$.position_z')::float           as position_z
    from source,
         json_each(raw_response->'$.heartbeats') as hb
)

select
    *,
    now()::timestamp as created_at
from expanded

with player_days as (
    select distinct
        player_id,
        date_trunc('day', event_datetime::timestamp) as play_date,
        date_trunc('month', event_datetime::timestamp) as year_month,
        country
    from "synthetic"."leap_stage"."fact_session"
),

ranked_days as (
    select
        player_id,
        year_month,
        play_date,
        country,
        row_number() over (partition by player_id, year_month order by play_date) as rn
    from player_days
),

groups as (
    select
        player_id,
        year_month,
        play_date,
        country,
        rn,
        date_diff('day', date '1970-01-01', play_date) - rn as grp
    from ranked_days
),

streaks as (
    select
        player_id,
        year_month,
        country,
        grp,
        count(*) as consecutive_days
    from groups
    group by player_id, year_month, country, grp
),

max_streaks as (
    select
        player_id,
        year_month,
        country,
        max(consecutive_days) as max_consecutive_days_played
    from streaks
    group by player_id, year_month, country
)

select * from max_streaks

with team_pairs as (
    select
        a.session_id,
        a.event_datetime,
        a.team_id as team_1_id,
        b.team_id as team_2_id,
        sqrt(
            power(a.centroid_x - b.centroid_x, 2) +
            power(a.centroid_y - b.centroid_y, 2) +
            power(a.centroid_z - b.centroid_z, 2)
        ) as distance
    from "synthetic"."leap_stage"."stage_centroids" a
    join "synthetic"."leap_stage"."stage_centroids" b
      on a.session_id = b.session_id
     and a.event_datetime = b.event_datetime
     and a.team_id < b.team_id
),

distance_flags as (
    select
        *,
        case when distance <= 30 then 1 else 0 end as is_close
    from team_pairs
),

ordered as (
    select
        *,
        lag(is_close) over (partition by session_id, team_1_id, team_2_id order by event_datetime) as prev_is_close,
        lag(event_datetime) over (partition by session_id, team_1_id, team_2_id order by event_datetime) as prev_event_datetime
    from distance_flags
),

-- Mark boundaries of new groups when:
-- 1) This is the first row (prev_is_close is null), OR
-- 2) Previous was not close AND current is close (conflict starts), OR
-- 3) Gap between this and previous event is > cooldown and previous was not close (long break)
group_boundaries as (
    select
        *,
        case 
          when prev_is_close is null then 1
          when is_close = 1 and prev_is_close = 0 then 1
          when extract(epoch from event_datetime - prev_event_datetime) > 60 and prev_is_close = 0 then 1
          else 0
        end as new_group_flag
    from ordered
),

grouped as (
    select
        *,
        sum(new_group_flag) over (partition by session_id, team_1_id, team_2_id order by event_datetime rows unbounded preceding) as conflict_group
    from group_boundaries
),

-- Filter only rows inside conflicts (is_close=1) or within cooldown after conflict ended
-- Because we want to include the cooldown period after last close heartbeat as part of conflict duration
final_conflict as (
    select
        session_id,
        team_1_id,
        team_2_id,
        conflict_group,
        event_datetime,
        is_close,
        lead(event_datetime) over (partition by session_id, team_1_id, team_2_id, conflict_group order by event_datetime) as next_event_datetime
    from grouped
    where conflict_group > 0
),

-- Calculate conflict window start and end times
conflict_windows as (
    select
        session_id,
        team_1_id,
        team_2_id,
        conflict_group,
        min(event_datetime) as conflict_start,
        -- Extend conflict end by cooldown seconds after last close heartbeat
        max(
            case 
                when next_event_datetime is null then event_datetime + interval '60 seconds'
                else next_event_datetime
            end
        ) as conflict_end
    from final_conflict
    group by session_id, team_1_id, team_2_id, conflict_group
),

-- Remove conflicts with zero or negative duration (just in case)
cleaned_conflicts as (
    select
        session_id,
        team_1_id,
        team_2_id,
        conflict_start,
        conflict_end
    from conflict_windows
    where conflict_end > conflict_start
)
